<div>
  <p>ArangoDB is available as Docker container. In order to install the stand-alone version use</p>
  <pre>
    docker run -p 8529:8529 -e ARANGO_ROOT_PASSWORD=openSesame @DOCKER_IMAGE@
  </pre>
  <p>
    You should check the
    <a href="https://docs.arangodb.com/3.4/Manual/Deployment/Docker/" target="_blank">Docker Deployment</a>
    section in the documentation about running ArangoDB in container
    and how to persist your data under Docker.
  </p>
</div>
